#Project Name#: Spatial Analysis for World Bank Urban Heat Management

#Client: The World Bank Economic Group

Problem: 
This project aims to help cities implement 3-30-300 framework heat mitigation strategies with consideration for social vulnerability and the urban heat island effect. Using spatial analysis techniques, we empower planners and advocates with varying degrees of access to robust data to champion climate change mitigation in their communities. Our solution is threefold: 
1. Producing a technical manual so cities can reproduce our analysis
2. Building a dashboard so analysts can communicate with local policymakers
3. Developing a report so future teams can build upon this work

